reviews.text: My first visit there for the roasted goose. Tastes delicious. Value for money too.
Flavorful congee, smooth and lots of sliced fresh fish (careful of the bones). No frills restaurants, quick and efficient service.
its taste was not bad but a little bit dirty

Unexpected gem found. We were looking for a nearby famous congee stall but it wasn't open. Stumble upon 富记 by accident and we were pleasantly surprised. The congee was tasty and the roast goose was even better then the 1star Michelin! We also ordered a claypot chicken w mushroom which flavourful. Don't expect fancy deco or ambience...
I had a plain porridge and it was fabulous! Thick and flavourful.

result.adr_address: G/F No, 104 Fa Yuen St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: G/F No, 104 Fa Yuen St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: Fu Kee Restaurant Co Ltd

reviews.text: Very very good service snd good cooking foof

I saw this hole-in-the-wall place in a list of the top places that the locals love. True enough, the food here was 10/10. There's en English menu for tourists, by the way. 

1. They're known for their congee. It's tasty and rich in flavor.
2. They have good roasted duck! It's also a must-try.
3. Their salt and pepper spare ribs were delicious.
4. The restaurant staff may seem to be un-friendly but they'll serve your food well and try their best to answer your questions. They only seem unfriendly because they can hardly speak English but nevertheless, they'll accomodate you nicely enough.
5. Try their fried noodles.
6. The restaurant itself is small and can probably accommodate less than 30 persons.

Go to Fu Kee for some authentic Cantonese dining experience.
Tried the roast goose and century egg porridge - very satisfying! This place is a hidden gem

result.adr_address: 香港旺角花園街104號
result.name: 富記粥品

reviews.text: 非常好吃😋
好吃👍
富記粥品是老店70年代我在上海街其老店幫襯過多年也不知開業了多久，搬到花園街也有廿年左右，其及第粥&及第湯出名燒味也不錯但坐位簡陋看來不舒服，名店就是這樣!
十分之難食白切雞不好食少肉多骨牛肉湯飯一啲味都冇只有水買牛肉完全沒有色澤自己落些雞粉好食過佢唔會再有第二次幫襯只可以用兩個字你形容垃圾
